The paper discusses game theory and its applications in agent-based simulations and institutional analysis, which are all relevant to computer science. The use of topology and ontology also suggests a focus on mathematical and computational methods. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Other possible sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity), as these fields also involve game theory and computational methods.
